rComments: Not the most organized professor, and more concerned with maintaining a certain course average (a low one at that) than actually helping students understand the material and succeed. The essay instructions were also vague and unclear and many students found it to be marked harshly.

rComments: Super detailed lectures, need a solid bio background even though it's a psych course, tests are v short so hard to get marks, prof isn't v accessible outside of class - prof is a good teacher tho, just content is super heavy

good at conveying the material during class! But her tests are mostly Short Answer and some of them are ambigious. You could write everything you know about a topic and still not be able to get 6/6 for a question.  That was the deal breaker for me and shes not great at letting you entertain remarks. Id say, take other PSY courses, I have a 3.7gpa
